article.headline: Murray St. 79, Jacksonville St. 65
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Ala. (AP) -- Danero Thomas had 20 points to help lead Murray State to a 79-65 victory over Jacksonville State Tuesday night. The Racers (4-3, 1-1 Ohio Valley Conference) grabbed the lead with 16:52 to go in the first half on a 3-pointer by Tyler Holloway and never let the Gamecocks (2-7, 0-2 OVC) get ahead, widening the margin to as many as 17 points several times during the game. Three other Murray State players joined Thomas in double figure scoring. Holloway had 14, Tony Easley had 12 and Ray George added 11. Easley also snagged 10 rebounds, giving him a double-double. Amadou Mbodji led the Gamecocks with 14 points. J.J. Wesley and Will Ginn had 11 points apiece, and Nick Murphy added 10 more.
